cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI 

The paper discusses methodological issues related to the evaluation of unsupervised binary code construction methods for nearest neighbor search, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the comparison of different methods, which falls under the scope of machine learning (LG) and multimedia (MM). Finally, the paper proposes conditions for fair comparison, which is related to evaluation methodology and could be relevant to various sub-categories, such as cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms).
